title: Sar Asiab-e Yusefi
text: Sar Asiab-e Yusefi (, also <a href="Romanize">Romanize</a>d as Sar Āsīāb-e Yūsefī; also known as Sar Āsīāb) is a village in <a href="Sar%20Asiab-e%20Yusefi%20Rural%20District">Sar Asiab-e Yusefi Rural District</a>, <a href="Bahmai-ye%20Garmsiri%20District">Bahmai-ye Garmsiri District</a>, <a href="Bahmai%20County">Bahmai County</a>, <a href="Kohgiluyeh%20and%20Boyer-Ahmad%20Province">Kohgiluyeh and Boyer-Ahmad Province</a>, <a href="Iran">Iran</a>. At the 2006 census, its population was 1,015, in 191 families.
